fields.description:
I downloaded sdog's favicon.ico to my local machine to upload to a new instance.

{{/secure/admin/jira/EditLookAndFeel.jspa}} returned the error:

{noformat}
Failed to upload image from file favicon.ico.

The MIME type image/vnd.microsoft.icon is unsupported. PNG, JPG and GIF images are the only supported formats.
{noformat}

When I go to the Issue Navigator and run the following query:

{noformat}assignee = currentUser() AND resolution = unresolved ORDER BY priority DESC, created ASC{noformat}


Issues that are closed appear as "open", and issues that are resolved appear as "unresolved", but when I click those specific issues to go to their page, it clearly says their resolution is: "Fixed" and their status is "Closed".

When try to change issue workflow or status, you will receive an error similar to the following:
{noformat}
HTTP Status 404 - Could not execute action 
{noformat}

The workaround is to disable and re-enable the JIRA Charting plugin.

Via a customer:

{quote}
What our team really needs is when a client sends an email with a request in it...there's a button somewhere I can click that automatically creates a ticket with the content and attachments of the email (and a link back to it) and maybe some quick entries, like an assignee and due date. Producteev did a pretty good job at that.

Forwarding it to an email address that JIRA monitors will, eventually, get it into the system in some form or another, but again that doesn't really strike me as integration, and then you still have to switch over to JIRA and find the item to fill in stuff like assignees and due dates (I know you can use filters to do some of that...).
{quote}

If the subject of an email contains a letter outside of ascii (such as 'é') then it will be moved to the spam folder within the JIRA Studio installation of procmail instead of adding a comment to a ticket or creating a ticket. The subject line according to the procmail.log will start like this:
{code}
Subject: =?ISO-8859-1?Q?Re=3A_=5BJIRA_Studio=5D_=28MDH=2D11=29_Test
{code}
As opposed to the expected:
{code}
Subject: Re: [JIRA Studio] (MDH-11) Test
{code}
